            <h1>My Story</h1>
            <p>In the summer of 2019 I graduated with a degree in Film Studies. I relentlessly spent my time applying for video editor jobs in the hopes of one day becoming a documentary video editor, however I felt so defeated as it seemed almost impossible to break into the industry. One day I vividly remember applying for a job that required HTML skills.</p>
            <p>Puzzled as to what ‘HTML’ even was I scoured the google for answers. That day I went down the rabbit hole of coding and instantly became obsessed. Day by day I began developing my knowledge about coding and the Tech industry. I decided to pause searching for video editor jobs and explore this new found interest - or should I say obsession.</p>
            <p>This led to me learning how code independently but felt like I needed to be taught and guidance to elecerate my learning. I enrolled in a Fullstack Coding Bootcamp and whilst completing my group project I became fixated on UI design. I was tasked with designing an app completely from scratch and immediately fell in love the entire processes of designing. It as if I was going through an awakening (again). After graduating from the bootcamp I concluded that I wanted to delve into the world of UI Design and see what oppouritities await me. I hope to create a positive impact in the Tech community and empower people who wish to make a career switch.</p>
         </div>
